<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,474,645]" pageId="7" pageNumber="275">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,547,573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="275">Remarks.</emphasis>
First records from North 
<collectingCountry box="[611,739,547,573]" name="Macedonia" pageId="7" pageNumber="275">Macedonia</collectingCountry>
. This Western Palaearctic species has been known from 
<collectingCountry name="Russia" pageId="7" pageNumber="275">Russia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[198,401,583,609]" country="Russia" name="Volgograd" pageId="7" pageNumber="275">Volgograd Oblast</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[421,511,583,609]" name="Ukraine" pageId="7" pageNumber="275">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[567,671,583,609]" name="Germany" pageId="7" pageNumber="275">Germany</collectingCountry>
so far (
<bibRefCitation author="Yu, D. S. &amp; van Achterberg, C. &amp; Horstmann, K." box="[758,925,583,609]" pageId="7" pageNumber="275" refId="ref7112" refString="Yu, D. S., van Achterberg, C. &amp; Horstmann, K. (2016) Taxapad 2016, Ichneumonoidea 2015. Nepean, Ontario. Database on flash-drive. Available from: http: // www. taxapad. com" type="url" year="2016">
Yu 
<emphasis box="[800,850,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="275">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
). This new record from the Balkan Peninsula represents its southernmost known locality.
</paragraph>
